SIMPLE: umpteen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: umpteen
<hw>ump"teen</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>An indefinite number, usu. more
than ten and less than one hundred; a lot. Often used hyperbolically,
and usually expressing the notion of <sig>more than the usual
number</sig> or <sig>more than I would like</sig>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧I've told you <xex>umpteen</xex> times not
to do that.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>umpteenth</ent>⟦br⟧
